fields.description:
I was doing an assignment over test case writing. So I chose JIRA's free trial registration form to write test cases. I have performed simple test case over form validation. Found out comparatively weak validation has been used on the form. Though it's not a major issue, just wanted to share my thoughts. I have used the following values..
 # *Email address* - %%@12.abc -> {color:#de350b}email field shouldn't accept this kind of special characters only email address. There should be an inline error message.{color}
 # *Password* - 1*250 -> {color:#de350b}No boundary value policy was applied here. used 250 characters of password.{color}
 # *First Name* - % -> {color:#de350b}Name field shouldn't accept special characters only.{color}
 # *Last Name* - & -> {color:#de350b}Name field shouldn't accept special characters only.{color}

